# Prisma Schema Conventions

- Edit Prisma schema with minimal, intentional changes; avoid touching unrelated models or enums.
- Keep datasource and generator configuration unchanged unless explicitly requested.
- Preserve model naming and mappings already in use (for example `@@map("articles")`, `@@map("works")`).
- Keep relational integrity intact when editing fields:
  - required foreign keys remain required unless requested otherwise
  - `onDelete` behavior should not change without explicit instruction
- For blog domain, `Article` is the source of truth (no separate `Blog` model).
- Preserve `ArticleStatus` enum values unless explicitly asked to evolve workflow.
- Add migrations only when schema changes are requested; avoid speculative migration edits.
- Prefer backward-compatible schema evolution and avoid destructive changes unless requested.
